-- Brisa Is Selling 15 Million Shares in Brazil's CCR for About $423 Million
-- B y   J o a o   L i m a
-- 2010-10-14T22:46:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/brisa-is-selling-15-million-shares-in-brazil-s-ccr-for-about-423-million.html
Brisa-Auto Estradas de Portugal SA,
Portugal’s biggest toll-road operator, said it’s selling 15.1
million shares in Brazilian highway operator Companhia de
Concessoes Rodoviarias for about 300 million euros.  The stake in CCR is being sold at about 46 reais a share,
Brisa said today in a filing posted on the website of Portugal’s
securities regulator. The sale is being carried out by Banco
Santander SA.   Brisa Chief Executive Officer Vasco de Mello in September
said the planned sale of the company’s 16.35 percent stake in
CCR will will be completed this year.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joao Lima at 
 jlima1@bloomberg.net  